# Student Management System – Task Report

While working on this project, I learned many basic concepts of Python programming. I practiced using variables, loops, conditional statements, functions, lists, and dictionaries. I also learned how to save data in a JSON file and load it again when the program starts. This helped me understand how real applications store information permanently.

One challenge I faced was figuring out how to keep student records saved after closing the program. At first, the data disappeared every time I restarted the application. After learning about file handling, I used a JSON file to store the records, which solved the problem.

Another challenge was handling invalid user input. For example, if a user entered text instead of a number for age, the program could crash. To solve this, I used try-except blocks to catch errors and display a message instead of stopping the program.

I also learned the importance of organizing code into functions. Creating separate functions for adding, viewing, searching, updating, and deleting students made the program easier to read and manage.

Overall, this project was a great learning experience. It improved my understanding of Python fundamentals and gave me confidence in building small applications. It also helped me understand concepts that will be useful in future studies related to Data Science and Machine Learning.
